History ofthe JLS
The original Jenny Lind Singers were founded in 1970 at Malvern Girls' Coll=
ege by their Head of Music, Eric Hemery, together with Elaine Hugh-Jones, a=
 well-known localcomposer and teacher of music at MGC. Pieces were sung by =
that group on arecord made by MGC in 1973, but they later ceased to exist.
In 2013, atthe invitation of the Malvern Civic Society, the Jenny Lind Sing=
ers werere-founded by Lynne Lindner, then the Director of Music at Malvern =
St JamesGirls=E2=80=99 School, and initially comprised singers whom Lynne h=
ad taught, some ofwhom were still at the school, while others had gone on t=
o Music Colleges orUniversity.

The group nowcomprises local adult female singers, many of them professiona=
l orsemi-professional musicians, and with the continued participation in so=
meconcerts, notably the group=E2=80=99s Christmas concerts, of trained sing=
ers who arepast pupils of Lynne=E2=80=99s.

The JLS are delighted to haveas their patron Countess Dr Inga Lewenhaupt, f=
ormer Chair of the Jenny LindSociety of Sweden.

Their regularaccompanist is local professional pianist Tim Sidford, and the=
y have also beenaccompanied by harpists Nia Evans and Anwen Mai Thomas.


